<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-424-745  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 424 745.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Sept 11 1990 v4 n30 p22(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mac satellite file transfer takes off: Engage launches $2,495SyncSatellite. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wylie, Margie.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Engage Communication Inc's SynchSatellite satellite communicationssystem will allow the transmission of Macintosh files viasatellite to the most remote parts of the planet.andP;  The packageincludes an AppleTalk hardware router and the software for sendingand receiving files through shared commercial communicationssatellites.andP;  The system transmits files at 64Kbps, with athroughput of about 400Kbytes per minute, about four to six timesthe speed of a 9,600-bps modem.andP;  Prices for the satellite servicesare available from ATandamp;T and other commercial vendors.andP;  TheSynchSatellite communications package lists for $2,495.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Engage Communication Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (equipment and supplies)Engage Communication SynchSatellite (Computer communicationsequipment) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSatellite Communications.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   SynchSatellite features. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Engage launches $2,495 SyncSatelliteandM;By Margie WylieandM;Aptos, Calif.andP;  -- Sending Macintosh files via satellite to even the remotestreaches of the world will soon be possible with SyncSatellite, a satellitecommunications system from Engage Communication Inc.andM;The $2,495 package, including software and an AppleTalk hardware router, letsusers send and receive files through shared commercial communicationssatellites.andM;&quot;To send a file, you just connect our box directly or via a leased line to anuplink service facility, sometimes called a teleport,&quot; said Rod Williams,director of marketing at Engage.andP;  &quot;It's then sent through a satellite dishvia microwave technology to a multichannel commercial satellite.andP;  From there,it can be broadcast simultaneously to multiple SyncSatellite-equippeddestinations, through another teleport or to a private receiving facilitycalled an earth station.&quot;andM;The system transmits files at 64 Kbps per second, yielding a throughput ofapproximately 400 Kbytes per minute -- about four to six times the throughputof a 9,600-bps modem, according to Engage.andP;  At destination sites, Macsrunning MultiFinder can receive the files transparently in the backgroundthrough a Control Panel device (cdev).andM;Prices for satellite services, available from American Telephone andamp; TelegraphCo. and other commercial vendors, vary widely depending on location and typeof service, Engage said.andP;  One North American service offers unlimited uplinkand downlink capabilities for about $8,800 per month; users with more-limitedneeds can get as-needed service and send a 1-Mbyte file to 10 locationsovernight for $50, roughly one-third the cost of standard overnight deliveryservices, according to Engage.andM;Target markets for the product, which is due by the end of the year, includecorporate customers who need to quickly send files to multiple sites andeducators delivering courseware to remote sites, especially in underdevelopedcountries.andP;  Last month, at a higher-education conference in Vancouver,British Columbia, Engage joined Apple and Farallon Computing Inc. ofEmeryville, Calif., in demonstrating the use of SyncSatellite with Farallon'sMediaTracks and Timbuktu Remote software.andM;Engage also is working with INS, a New York-based news and graphics service,to provide digitized photos and other graphics via SyncSatellite tonewspapers.andM;In the past, Mac users might unknowingly have taken advantage of satellitecommunications in the course of using huge packet-switched networks, butSyncSatellite may be the first commercially available direct Mac-to-Mac filetransfer package for use with satellite services.andM;Engage Communication Inc. is located at 9053 Soquel Drive, Suite 201, Aptos,Calif.andP;  95003; (408) 688-1021.andO;</TEXT></DOC>